---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Portfolio">

  <section class="relative bg-gray-950 border-b border-gray-800 overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/blueprint-hero-bg.png"
      alt=""
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover object-bottom opacity-40"
    />
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 text-center">
      <p class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-8">
        Selected Work
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-[1.15] tracking-tight mb-8 text-white">
        Portfolio
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Open-source software, systems, and applied projects.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

    <div class="border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">USLM Parser</h2>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/jesoderberg/uslm-parser"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-xs font-medium text-blue-400 bg-blue-900/30 px-3 py-1 rounded-full whitespace-nowrap hover:bg-blue-900/50 transition-colors"
        >
          GitHub →
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Python · XML · MIT License · 2026</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Open-source Python framework for automated parsing of United States Legislative Markup (USLM) XML
        the standard format used by the Government Publishing Office for federal legislation. Removes human
        transcription error from the legislative data pipeline entirely.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm">
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Efficiency gain</p>
          <p class="font-bold text-white">4.8M–9.6M×</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Cross-format error</p>
          <p class="font-bold text-white">0.0%</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Validation types</p>
          <p class="font-bold text-white">38 → 103</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">False positive rate</p>
          <p class="font-bold text-white">&gt;99% → &lt;1%</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 mt-5">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">USACE Analytical Notebooks</h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 bg-gray-900 px-3 py-1 rounded-full whitespace-nowrap">
          Internal
        </span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Python · pandas · Jupyter · 2025–2026</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Suite of analytical notebooks for national Civil Works program and project management at USACE HQ.
        Automates schedule deviation analysis, milestone tracking, and T&amp;I (Technically and Independently)
        workload reporting across thousands of active studies and construction projects.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm">
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Studies analyzed</p>
          <p class="font-bold text-white">114 records</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Construction projects</p>
          <p class="font-bold text-white">718 records</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Notebooks</p>
          <p class="font-bold text-white">10+</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-3">
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Libraries</p>
          <p class="font-bold text-white">pandas · NumPy · matplotlib</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 mt-5">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Geospatial Mapping &amp; Visualization</h2>
        <span class="text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 bg-gray-900 px-3 py-1 rounded-full whitespace-nowrap">
          Selected work
        </span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Python · GeoPandas · cartopy · ArcGIS · matplotlib</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Geospatial analysis and map production spanning federal regulatory programs, Civil Works project locations,
        and FEMA disaster declaration data. Work ranges from national-scale choropleth mapping to county-level
        emergency impact visualization.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span><span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">National Capital Region map</span>, county-level base map built from ArcGIS REST services via GeoPandas</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span><span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">FEMA disaster declarations</span>, hurricane impact choropleth maps, 2022–2024 DR declarations</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span><span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">Civil Works project locations</span>, CW location hierarchy visualization across the national portfolio</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span><span class="text-gray-200 font-medium">National wetland data standards</span>, co-authored the FGDC federal standard governing wetland spatial data nationwide</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
